theorem Topology.interiorCompl_subset_compl_closureInterior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (Aᶜ) ⊆ (closure (interior A))ᶜ := by
  intro x hxIntCompl
  by_cases hMem : x ∈ closure (interior A)
  ·
    -- If `x` lies in both sets, we contradict their established disjointness.
    have hInter : x ∈ closure (interior A) ∩ interior (Aᶜ) :=
      ⟨hMem, hxIntCompl⟩
    have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [Topology.closureInterior_inter_interiorCompl_eq_empty (A := A)] using hInter
    exact this.elim
  ·
    -- Otherwise, `x` belongs to the complement of `closure (interior A)`.
    simpa [Set.compl_def] using hMem

theorem Topology.P2_union_three {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B C : Set X}
    (hA : Topology.P2 (A := A)) (hB : Topology.P2 (A := B)) (hC : Topology.P2 (A := C)) :
    Topology.P2 (A := A ∪ B ∪ C) := by
  -- First, combine `A` and `B`.
  have hAB : Topology.P2 (A := A ∪ B) :=
    Topology.P2_union (A := A) (B := B) hA hB
  -- Now union the result with `C`.
  simpa [Set.union_assoc] using
    (Topology.P2_union (A := A ∪ B) (B := C) hAB hC)
